# Supabase Migration Filename Numbering

When creating a new migration in `supabase/migrations/`, always increment the final numeric suffix from the latest existing migration file.

- Inspect existing migration filenames in `supabase/migrations/`.
- Identify the highest trailing numeric segment.
- Name the new migration with the next number (highest + 1).
- Keep the existing prefix/timestamp format used by this project.

## Example

If latest is `20260322000000_add_team_to_tours.sql`, next should be:

- `20260322000001_<description>.sql`

Do not reuse or skip numbers unless explicitly requested.
